# =============================================================================
#  CRITICAL — READ CLAUDE.md: "No Source Code on GitHub — EVER".
#
#  This GitHub repo (kvrnl/claude-assist) exists ONLY to deliver installer
#  releases. Source code, scripts, build configs, and project files must NEVER
#  be committed or pushed. The compiled installer .exe is delivered via the
#  GitHub Releases API — never through git.
#
#  Strategy: ignore EVERYTHING by default, then explicitly allow only the
#  handful of files that are safe to publish. This makes an accidental
#  `git add -A` structurally incapable of staging source code.
# =============================================================================

# Ignore everything by default.
*

# ...except these explicitly-allowed, safe-to-publish files:
!.gitignore
!README.md
!LICENSE

# NOTE: SECURITY.md and PRIVACY.md are intentionally NOT allow-listed yet —
# publishing them is a decision for the user to make. Add `!SECURITY.md` /
# `!PRIVACY.md` here only after confirming they should be public.
